commit.message:
Fix detection of when Spotify exits

Spotify is now spawning multiple processes so the existing code to
detect when spotify exits didn't work right any more.
Tested with spotify 0.9.10.17
Tested with spotify-0.9.4.183

Use base64 instead of utf-8 for icon cache hash

With utf-8 we'd see errors like:

UnicodeDecodeError: 'ascii' codec can't decode byte 0xc4 in position 10:
ordinal not in range(128)

with certain files containing non-ASCII characters. Changing the
encoding to base64 has fixed the issue with these files.

Properly exit when Spotify exits

There was an issue due to the 'pidof' syntax, the script was calling
'pidof /usr/bin/spotify' and not receiving any output. Calling
'pidof spotify' returns the correct process ID allowing the script
to properly detect when Spotify exits.
